{"name":"Specialized Faith","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 30\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 84\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 84\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Priests who elect to embrace a specialized faith develop supplementary abilities. Each ability is particular to and granted by the deity that the priest exclusively venerates, as noted in <strong>Table 47</strong>. A breach of faith or alignment may result in the loss of these abilities, as best adjudicated by the referee. Priests of specialized faith oft are regarded as zealots; even practitioners of similar beliefs may judge them as eccentrics.</p>\n<p>[<strong>Table 47: Priest Abilities by Deity</strong>&nbsp;-- see&nbsp;<strong>Player's Manual</strong>, p.84]</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"priest","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.PLRVII62fOX22khR"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679251242630,"modifiedTime":1681579119882,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"1cutfkKSmz7QIJwx","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Sorcery","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 33\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Priests memorize and cast spells, but they do not maintain spell books; rather, they might bear the scriptures of their faiths in prayer books, on sacred scrolls, or on graven tablets. The number and levels of spells cast per day are charted on <strong>Table 46</strong>, though priests of high wisdom gain bonus spells cast per day (see <strong>Chapter 3: Statistics</strong>, <em>wisdom</em>). For example, a 4th-level priest with 13 wisdom can cast five level 1 spells and three level 2 spells per day.</p>\n<p>Priests begin their careers with knowledge of four level 1 spells, sacred mysteries revealed through initiation into a sect or cult devoted to an otherworldly power, deific being, or ethos. These spells are drawn from the <strong>Cleric Spell List</strong> (see <strong>Chapter 7: Sorcery</strong>, <strong>Table 99</strong>). Priests develop four new spells at each level gain. Typically, they are acquired via spiritual revelation, otherworldly favour, or the piecing together of abstract theologies. Such spells are learnt automatically, with no need of qualification rolls, but they must be of castable levels (see <strong>Table 46</strong>).</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Initial no. of spells known: &times;4</li>\n<li>No. of spells gained per level: &times;4</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Additional spells may be learnt outside of level training, but the process is more arduous (see <strong>Chapter 7: Sorcery</strong>, <em>acquiring new spells</em>).</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"priest","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679252111719,"modifiedTime":1681579119882,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"3Mi4CzjVjZbMW1vK","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Scroll Writing","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 30\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 32\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To scribe a known spell onto a scroll, creating a single-use magical device at a cost of 500 gp + 100 gp per spell level. Materials vary: Some priests engrave thin tablets of stone, whereas others use vellum or parchment, a fine quill, and sorcerer&rsquo;s ink, such as sepia. This involved process requires one week per spell level and must be completed on consecrated ground, such as a shrine, fane, or temple.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"priest","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.5svHxLHi8sIn35Uj"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679251303706,"modifiedTime":1681579119882,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"HFvsabOoXvI9XiWW","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Daemonwrack","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 30\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 84\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>At 9th level, once per week, conduct a powerful ritual that dismisses or beckons a d&aelig;mon or other netherworldly being. This ability functions as the <em>dismissal</em> spell, except that it applies only to d&aelig;mons and their ilk.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"priest","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.PLRVII62fOX22khR"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679251242630,"modifiedTime":1681579119881,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"VFNzZZitiEiT16BH","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Scroll Use","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 30\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To decipher and invoke scrolls with spells from the <strong>Cleric Spell List</strong> (see <strong>Chapter 7: Sorcery</strong>, <strong>Table 99</strong>), unless the scroll was created by a thaumaturgical sorcerer (one who casts magician or magician subclass spells).</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"priest","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.PLRVII62fOX22khR"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679251242630,"modifiedTime":1681579119881,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"iwOtA8Cf3Ek98Feo","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Turn Undead","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 33\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 84\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Like clerics, priests<span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\"> can exert control over the undead and some d&aelig;monic beings, causing them to flee and/or cower. Evil priests can opt instead to compel the submission and service of these foul creatures. In either case, the priest must do the following:</span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<ul>\n<li>Stand before the undead (within 30 feet)</li>\n<li>Speak boldly a commandment whilst displaying a holy symbol</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The referee must cross-reference the <span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">priest</span>&rsquo;s <em>turning ability</em> (TA) with the <em>Undead Type</em> to determine the <span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">priest</span>&rsquo;s chance of success. The referee may ask the player to roll a d12 to determine the outcome, or the result may be fixed. The results are as follows:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">d12 score equal to/less than the number indicated: <strong>T (turned)</strong></span></li>\n<li>d12 score greater than the number indicated: <strong>NT (not turned)</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 33\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p><strong>Undead Turning Definitions:</strong><br>The following definitions apply to Table 13:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\"><strong>NT (not turned):</strong> the undead are beyond the priest&rsquo;s power to affect.</span></li>\n<li><strong>T (turned):</strong> 2d6 undead are compelled to cower/flee for 1 turn unless attacked.</li>\n<li><strong>D (destroyed):</strong> 2d6 undead are exorcized/destroyed, crumbling to dust.</li>\n<li><strong>UD (ultimate destruction):</strong> 1d6+6 undead are exorcized/destroyed, crumbling to dust.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>N.B.: Priests of above-average charisma (15+) are more commanding; hence, their chance-in-twelve of success is improved by one (+1); e.g., a 4-in-12 chance becomes 5-in-12 (see <strong>Chapter 3: Statistics</strong>, <em>charisma</em>).</p>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 33\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p><strong>Frequency of Undead Turning:</strong> This ability can be used a number of times per day equal to the character&rsquo;s TA; however, the <span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">priest</span> can make but one attempt per encounter unless a second wave of undead arrive.</p>\n<p>[<strong>Table 13: Turn Undead</strong> -- see <strong>Player's Manual</strong>, p. 33]</p>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 34\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p><strong>How to Turn Multiple Undead Types:</strong> If multiple kinds of undead are met in a single encounter, only one d12 roll is required. The same result is applied to each <em>Undead Type</em>. Those of the lowest <em>Undead Type</em> are affected first, unless the sorcerer specifically targets a single creature, in which case only that creature potentially is affected (e.g., if a <strong>vampire</strong> stands at the fore of a pack of <strong>zombies</strong>, the <span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">priest</span> might step forth, holy symbol raised, and speak a commandment of abolishment, pointing a holy symbol directly at the <strong>vampire</strong>).</p>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 34\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p><strong>Evil Command of Undead:</strong> A <span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">priest</span> of Evil alignment may opt to exercise control over the undead on a successful <em>turn undead</em> check. Such undead remain under the sorcerer&rsquo;s sway unless <em>turned</em> or <em>commanded</em> by another sorcerer of equal or greater turning ability. Up to 2 HD of undead per TA level can be controlled. If a Neutral <span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">priest</span> attempts to <em>command undead</em>, then he or she will have turned to a darker path, submitting to Evil and no longer of Neutral alignment; consequences may ensue.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"priest","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679252111719,"modifiedTime":1681579119882,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"j6qCkiJqMFha3TK5","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
